# PCR Amplification Protocol

## Overview

Standard PCR amplification of gene fragment using Taq DNA polymerase.

## Materials

- [ ] Template DNA (10-100 ng/μL)
- [ ] Forward primer (10 μM)
- [ ] Reverse primer (10 μM)
- [ ] Taq DNA polymerase (5 U/μL)
- [ ] 10× PCR buffer
- [ ] dNTPs (10 mM each)
- [ ] Nuclease-free water
- [ ] 0.2 mL PCR tubes

## Thermocycler Program

| Step | Temperature | Duration | Cycles |
|------|-------------|----------|--------|
| Initial denaturation | 95°C | 3 min | 1 |
| Denaturation | 95°C | 30 sec | 35 |
| Annealing | 58°C | 30 sec | 35 |
| Extension | 72°C | 1 min/kb | 35 |
| Final extension | 72°C | 5 min | 1 |
| Hold | 4°C | ∞ | - |

## Reaction Mix (25 μL)

| Component | Volume | Final |
|-----------|--------|-------|
| 10× Buffer | 2.5 μL | 1× |
| dNTPs | 0.5 μL | 200 μM |
| Forward primer | 1 μL | 0.4 μM |
| Reverse primer | 1 μL | 0.4 μM |
| Taq polymerase | 0.25 μL | 1.25 U |
| Template | 1-5 μL | 10-100 ng |
| Water | to 25 μL | - |

## Procedure

### 1. Prepare Reaction Mix

1. Thaw reagents on ice
2. Vortex and centrifuge all components
3. Prepare master mix (all components except template)

### 2. Aliquot and Add Template

1. Add 20 μL master mix to each tube
2. Add template DNA to respective tubes
3. Cap tubes and centrifuge briefly

### 3. Run PCR

1. Place tubes in thermocycler
2. Select and run the PCR program
3. After completion, store at 4°C

## Analysis

- Run 5 μL product on 1% agarose gel
- Expected band size: ~850 bp
- Visualize under UV with ethidium bromide
